{"sequence":47,"timestamp":"2026-04-29T03:30:12.908353981Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-2-56c8025a","body":"The two newly unignored `run stop` signal tests still have a startup race. In `tests/cli.rs:10558` and `tests/cli.rs:10878`, the bash helper is considered ready immediately after `spawn()`, but `run stop` can send SIGTERM before the shell has executed `trap '' TERM` or `trap 'rm -f \"$RALPH_PID_FILE\"; exit 0' TERM`. If that happens, the SIGKILL test may exit on SIGTERM instead of requiring SIGKILL, and the handoff test may not remove `run.pid`, reintroducing the exact CI flake this bead is meant to eliminate. Add an explicit ready-file handshake after installing each trap and wait for that file before invoking `run stop`.","classification":"fix_current_bead","dedup_key":"2b42cad28446551ada7e57648cb3a20ae7a06b5db03039a9ae9e2950a7513d5a","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"codex","model_id":"gpt-5.5-xhigh","reviewer_id":"reviewer-1"}],"run_id":"run-20260429001334","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
